#TextureTuesday #belifOnTheGo

Haven't we all been intrigued by products that claim to penetrate deep into the skin?🤔 After all, deeper the product gets into the skin, the more effective it must be, right? 

#TruthfulThursday: Actually, the skin serves as a protective barrier that prevents 🚫 the entry of microbes🔬and other harsh elements. 

Depending on the formulation and ingredients, skincare products help to strengthen the barrier 💪and retain moisture💧

You think if you suffer from oily acne prone skin, you should atleast be granted a wrinkle-free face! 

#MythBustingMonday Oily skin is just as prone to getting wrinkles. 

Multiple factors such as genetics🔬, lifestyle, sun exposure ⛅ play a role in ageing the skin. 

Eating a balanced diet 🥗, drinking plenty of water 💧, exercising 🏋️ and following a skincare routine consistently can slow down the process of ageing! 

Drop a 💙 if you found this post useful!

Who doesn’t love a good facial? 🥰 

While facials deep cleanse and add the necessary hydration💧 to the skin it is just a temporary fix!⌛ 

#TruthfulThursday For glowing ✨skin all year round, one needs to follow a skincare routine consistently. This includes selecting products🛍️ formulated especially for one’s skin type and concern.

#TruthfulThursday: What's more important than using sunscreen with SPF50? 🧴🤔

✅ Using a broad spectrum sunscreen (block those pesky UVA rays)

✅ Applying enough sunscreen (1/4 tsp or 3 fingerfuls for face + neck)

✅ Re-applying sunscreen every 2 hours (even when you're indoors!)
